                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13321488/comment/17173149",
                    "id": "17173149",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Lachrymatory",
                        "name": "Lachrymatory",
                        "key": "lachrymatory",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Nolo Ogbirner",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Rome"
                    },
                    "body": "From [https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/API_GetObject.html] , it seems that you can essentially replace the bucket name by the ARN (identifier for AWS entities) in your request and that's it.\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\n  *[Bucket|https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/API_GetObject.html#API_GetObject_RequestSyntax]*  \r\n\r\nThe bucket name containing the object.\r\n\r\nWhen using this API with an access point, you must direct requests to the access point hostname. The access point hostname takes the form _AccessPointName_-_AccountId_.s3-accesspoint._Region_.amazonaws.com. When using this operation using an access point through the AWS SDKs, you provide the access point ARN in place of the bucket name. For more information about access point ARNs, see [Using Access Points|https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/using-access-points.html] in the _Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide_.\r\n\r\nRequired: Yes",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Lachrymatory",
                        "name": "Lachrymatory",
                        "key": "lachrymatory",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
