                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Rome"
                    },
                    "body": "That's what I'm not exactly sure about. I tried looking at the C++ implementation but am unsure if it is just taking the bucket from \"bucket/key\" and passing that as the hostname to a REST GET request to S3. If it is, it should be fine but my initial tests with just replacing the ARN didn't work. The default hostname is Bucket.s3.amazonaws.com whereas with access point it is _AccessPointName_-_AccountId_.s3-accesspoint._Region_.amazonaws.com",
